<br>
&quot;- Increased stun shout duration to be comparable to other single target stun spells.&quot;<br>
<br>
Though the reasoning that Mythic used in their patch notes is flawed (instant stuns are lower duration for a reason), the increase to stun duration is valid because of the changes to resists since the minstrel class was first introduced. <br>
<br>
I think that the skald 30s insta-mez needs to be adjusted in the same manner. Since it's our only form of crowd control I don't think asking for a 50% increase to duration would be out of line.  <p>Eka, lvl 50 skald Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roimma@teamskald>Roimma</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/19/03 7:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=681.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald mez duration request for next TL report</span><hr size=1> I completly agree, if someone even has determination 1 it leaves our mez with not even enough time for our dd's to refresh before they can attack again. <p>Roimma - the cutest kobold skald on pendragon ^_^</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yolt>yolt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/25/03 11:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=681.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald mez duration request for next TL report</span><hr size=1> I'd love a longer mez, but on the other hand, it may be better for skalds if we focused on getting some additional abilities in our songs line instead of letting Mythic get away with just tweaking a few existing shouts and calling us good.<br>
<br>
In the big picture, skalds rarely have to be concerned about mez length unless dueling an enemy tank...and usually the best thing to do when fighting a tank is to kite anyway.<br>
<br>
Instead of a longer mez length, I'd rather see debuff shouts, haste chant, endurance boost, etc.  If skalds are given some attention in some other areas, the mez length will not be an issue.<br>
<br>
<br>
